│ THOUGHT: The assertion is triggered in ShuffleVectorInst::isSingleSourceMask because TTI’s                      │
│ improveShuffleKindFromMask uses a NumOpElts that doesn’t match the operands’ element count for a two-source     │
│ shuffle resulting in a smaller vector. In VectorCombine::foldShuffleOfSelects, we call TTI.getShuffleCost with  │
│ BaseTp = DstVecTy (the result type), while the mask indices refer to the concatenation of the two source        │
│ vectors (each with the select’s element count). For masks like <4,7> with two <4 x float> operands and a <2 x   │
│ float> result, passing BaseTp as <2 x float> causes NumOpElts=2, making indices 4 and 7 out-of-bounds. A simple │
│ and correct fix is to pass the source operand vector type (same as T1/T2/F1/F2 types) to getShuffleCost when    │
│ evaluating the shuffle costs in this fold, so improveShuffleKindFromMask sees the correct NumOpElts (4 here). I │
│ will modify VectorCombine.cpp to use the common operand vector type instead of DstVecTy for these               │
│ getShuffleCost calls.                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ sed -i '2060,2070{s/DstVecTy/C1VecTy/g;}' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp && sed -n             │
│ '2056,2072p' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp                                                    │
│ ```                                                                                                             │
