│ THOUGHT: The crash stems from improveShuffleKindFromMask calling                                                │
│ ShuffleVectorInst::isSelectMask/isSingleSourceMask with NumOpElts inferred from BaseTp, which can be smaller    │
│ than the number of elements referenced by the mask when folding shuffles that reduce vector size. To robustly   │
│ avoid the assertion, I will adjust improveShuffleKindFromMask to use an adjusted NumOpElts that is at least the │
│ mask length. Specifically, introduce NumOpEltsAdj = max(Mask.size(), NumOpElts) and use it for all              │
│ isSelectMask/isSingleSourceMask calls. This prevents out-of-bounds validation when masks reference elements     │
│ beyond BaseTp’s count.                                                                                          │
